current_guiding_trade_logic_source.calculation_directive: Calculate all technical indicators (e.g., EMA, RSI, ATR, Volume MA) from the raw kline data. Evaluate all strategy rules based on these calculations.
current_guiding_trade_logic_source.objective: Execute high-probability, short-term trades based on quantitative signals. Prioritize capital preservation and consistent, small gains. The primary goal is a profitable exit based on pre-calculated levels.

risk_management_protocol.description: Apply strict, quantitative rules for managing risk. Calculate all required values prior to trade entry.

stop_loss_placement_rule.description: Calculate the StopLossPrice from the entry price using the Average True Range (ATR) on the entry_timeframe to place it beyond recent noise.
stop_loss_placement_rule.rule: For BUYs: entryPrice - (ATR * atr_multiplier). For SELLs: entryPrice + (ATR * atr_multiplier).

profit_target_placement_rule.description: Calculate the TakeProfitPrice based on the StopLossPrice and the required_reward_to_risk_ratio to ensure a fixed risk-reward profile.
profit_target_placement_rule.rule: For BUYs: entryPrice + ((entryPrice - stopLossPrice) * required_reward_to_risk_ratio). For SELLs: entryPrice - ((stopLossPrice - entryPrice) * required_reward_to_risk_ratio).

profit_protection_rule.description: If triggered, move the stop loss to the entry price to secure the position from loss.

trade_entry_protocol.description: Evaluate the following confluence of conditions to justify opening a new position. A scoring system must be used to meet the minimum confidence threshold.

confluence_conditions.description: Verify price is on the side of the medium-term trend.
confluence_conditions.rule: For BUYs: price > EMA(45). For SELLs: price < EMA(45).

confluence_conditions.description: Verify short-term momentum aligns with medium-term trend.
confluence_conditions.rule: For BUYs: EMA(9) > EMA(21). For SELLs: EMA(9) < EMA(21).

confluence_conditions.description: Trigger an entry on a pullback to a short-term moving average.
confluence_conditions.rule: For BUYs: price tests and holds above EMA(9). For SELLs: price tests and holds below EMA(9).

confluence_conditions.description: Confirm momentum with RSI and ensure market is not in overbought/oversold conditions.
confluence_conditions.rule: For BUYs: RSI(14) > 50 AND RSI(14) < 70. For SELLs: RSI(14) < 50 AND RSI(14) > 30.

market_condition_filter.description: Apply these filters to ensure the market is in a suitable state for scalping. Do not trade if any filter condition is met.

volatility_filter.rule: DO NOT TRADE if ATR(14) is > 200% of its 45-period moving average. This avoids explosive, unpredictable volatility.

volume_filter.rule: DO NOT TRADE if Volume is < 75% of its 20-period moving average. This avoids illiquid market conditions.

trade_exit_protocol.description: Evaluate the following rules to govern the active management and closure of a position.

early_exit_conditions.rule: For a BUY, if a candle on the 'entry_timeframe' CLOSES below the structural support level used for entry, issue an immediate CLOSE_POSITION decision. Vice-versa for a SELL.
For a BUY, if RSI(14) on 'entry_timeframe' crosses below 40, issue a CLOSE_POSITION decision. For a SELL, if RSI crosses above 60.
If a trade has been open for 20 candles on the 'entry_timeframe' and has not achieved the 1:1 profit_protection_rule trigger, issue a CLOSE_POSITION decision.

analysis_parameters.description: Defines the kline data scope for analysis. Timeframes are relative to the trade type.

technical_constraints.description: Mandatory technical requirements for the bot's execution logic. Failure to comply will result in rejection.
technical_constraints.precision_adherence: All 'price' and 'quantity' values in the response MUST strictly adhere to the precision defined in `market_data.symbol_precision`.
technical_constraints.profitability_check: The calculated distance between `entryPrice` and `takeProfitPrice` must be greater than the round-trip commission cost. Use `market_data.commission_rates` to calculate this cost.

learning_directive.notes_format: Append a JSON object to 'ai_learnings_notes' after each trade with the following keys: {trade_id, outcome (win/loss/breakeven), exit_reason (stop_loss/take_profit/early_exit_condition), confidence_score_at_entry, market_notes (e.g., 'High volatility during London open')}
